==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tragical
<hw>Trag"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>tragicus</ets>, Gr.<?/: cf. F.
<ets>tragique</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to
tragedy; of the nature or character of tragedy; <as>as, a
<ex>tragic</ex> poem; a <ex>tragic</ex> play or
representation</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fatal to life; mournful; terrible; calamitous;
<as>as, the <ex>tragic</ex> scenes of the French
revolution</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Mournful; expressive of tragedy, the loss of life,
or of sorrow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Why look you still so stern and <qex>tragical</qex> ?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Trag"ic*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Trag"ic*al*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tragic</ent>⟦br⟧
